rd Burdon Haldane and a \u2018Liberal\u2019 Nation-in-Arms,\" in ''Militarism and the British Left, 1902\u20131914'' (Palgrave Macmillan, London, 2013) pp. 133\u2013155.\n* {{cite book | last = Koss | first = Stephen | authorlink = Stephen Koss | year = 1985 | title = Asquith | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=tBGGAAAAIAAJ | location = London | publisher = Hamish Hamilton | isbn = 978-0-231-06155-1| ref = harv}}\n*{{cite journal|last1=Langhorne|first1=Richard|title=VII. The Naval Question in Anglo-German Relations, 1912\u20131914|journal=The Historical Journal|volume=14|issue=2|year=1971|pages=359\u2013370|issn=0018-246X|doi=10.1017/S0018246X0000964X|jstor=2637960|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|first=H.C.G.|last=Matthew|title=Liberal Imperialists: The Ideas and Politics of a Post-Gladstonian elite|place=Oxford|date=1973|isbn=0198218427|ref=harv|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/liberalimperiali0000matt}}\n* {{cite ODNB|last=Matthew |first=H. C. G. |id=33643|title=Haldane, Richard Burdon, Viscount Haldane (1856\u20131928)|date=6 January 2011}}\n*{{cite journal|last1=Maurer|first1=John H.|title=The Anglo-German Naval Rivalry and Informal Arms Control, 1912-1914|journal=Journal of Conflict Resolution|volume=36|issue=2|year=1992|pages=284\u2013308|issn=0022-0027|doi=10.1177/0022002792036002004|jstor=174477|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Maurice|first= Frederick|ref=harv|title=Haldane: The Life of Viscount Haldane of Cloan|date=1937|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.526598|volume=Vol. 1: 1856 to 1915|publisher=Fabe and Faber|location=London}}\n* {{cite book|last=Maurice|first= Frederick|ref=harv|title=Haldane: The Life of Viscount Haldane of Cloan|date=1939|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.526599|volume=Vol. 2 1915-1928|publisher=Fabe and Faber|location=London}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=McKinstry|first=Leo |title=Rosebery: Statesman in Turmoil|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IyCDQgAACAAJ|year=2005|publish