n=0099575442|ref=harv|publisher=Chatto & Windus}}\n*{{cite journal|last1=Scott|first1=James Brown|title=Lord Haldane's Diary of Negotiations Between Germany and England in 1912|journal=The American Journal of International Law|volume=12|issue=3|year=1918|pages=589|issn=00029300|doi=10.2307/2188240|jstor=2188240|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Sommer|first=Dudley |title=Haldane of Cloan: his life and times|url=https://archive.org/details/haldaneofcloanhi0000somm|url-access=registration|year=1960|publisher=G. Allen & Unwin|oclc=75294052|location=London}}\n* Spiers, Edward M. ''Haldane: An Army Reformer'' (1980),  240pp.\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Tanner|first=Duncan |title=Political Change and the Labour Party 1900-1918|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2XWGuS25msYC&pg=PA45|year=2003|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-53053-8}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Vaughan|first=Frederick |title=Viscount Haldane: \"the Wicked Step-father of the Canadian Constitution\"|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yjfFmMQBR4kC|via=Osgoode Society for Canadian Legal History|date= 2010|publisher=University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-1-4426-4237-9}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Webb|first=Beatrice |authorlink=Beatrice Webb|title=Our Partnership|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.275455/page/n98|year=1948|publisher=Longman Green|isbn=978-0-521-20852-9}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Webb|first=Beatrice |authorlink=Beatrice Webb|title=The Diary of Beatrice Webb|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780860688464/page/344|year=1986|publisher=Virago|location=London|isbn=978-0-86068-845-7}}\n{{refend}}\n\n===Further reading===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|first=Duff|last=Cooper|title=Old Men Even Die|date=1963}}\n* {{cite book|last=Lyman|first=Richard W.|title=The First Labour Government|url=https://archive.org/details/firstlabourgover0000lyma|url-access=registration|publisher=Chapman & Hall|place=London|year=1957|isbn=9780846217848}}\n* {{cite book|last=